    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.9.36" />
                
                <fw type="curatorial">36</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">THE FRANK A. MUNSEY COMPANY
                        <lb/>
                    TWO-EIGHTY BROADWAY
                        <lb/>
                    NEW YORK</hi>
                        <lb/>
                
                    Munsey's Magazine
                        <lb/>
                    Argosy-All-Story Weekly
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>November 29, 1922</dateline>
                
                    <salute>My dear John:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I hear that you are coming to Washington early in March and that on February seventh, you will hurl something down the throats of the people in Cincinnati, after which you will come to New York and vicinity to see what you can see.</p>
                
                <p>If you show up in this neck of the woods without coming straight to my office the moment you get off the train, I'll have you arrested for vagrancy. You have got to give me at least twenty-four hours so that we can go away somewhere in the country and have a heart to heart conversation. It is a long time since we've met but I haven't lost sight of you.</p>
                
                <p>I was going to suggest that Enid send me a kiss but I don't see how you could deliver it. Let me know your plans. I write poetry myself, John, but I've never had the courage to send any to you.</p>
                
                <p>Best to all of you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Ever thine,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>RH Davis</signed>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Bancroft,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Nebraska.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <note>RHD L</note>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
